## Unit 3: Lesson 08 - Conditionals

# Background

After a brief online refresher with booleans students are introduced to some boolean producing keyboard input functions that they can use in conditionals to move sprites around the screen.

# Vocabulary
* **Boolean** - A value of either TRUE or FALSE
* **Conditionals** - Statements that only run under certain conditions.
* **Expression** - Any valid unit of code that resolves to a value.

# Commands 

### Sprites : 
|Command| Meaning| Example | Documentation |
|---|---| --- | --- |
|createSprite(x, y, width, height)|Creates a new rectangle sprite.|`var square = createSprite(200,300, 40, 40);`  | link |
|sprite.shapeColor| Property for the color of rectangle sprites|`sprite.shapeColor = color(230, 140, 93);`  | link |
|sprite.x| Property for x position of sprite| `sprite.x = randomNumber(0,400);` | link |
|sprite.y| Property for y position of sprite| `sprite.y = 200;` | link |
|sprite.width| Property for width of sprite| `sprite.width = randomNumber(0,100);` | link |
|sprite.height|Property for height of sprite| `sprite.height = 30;`  | link |
|sprite.rotation|Property for angle of rotation of sprite in degrees| `sprite.roation = randomNumber(0,360);` | link |

### Input : 
|Command| Meaning| Example | Documentation |
|---|---| --- | --- |
|mouseX|Gives the x position of the mouse|`sprite.x = mouseX;`  | link |
|mouseY|Gives the y position of the mouse|`sprite.y = mouseY;` | link |

